Girijana Vidyarthi Samakhya (GVS) flayed the State governmentâ€™s move to close down welfare hostels for weaker section students citing non-occupancy and expressed protest at the Jyotirao Phule statue in the city on Sunday.GVS activists led by president V. Sankar Naik submitted a mock representation to the Phule statue, seeking to draw his attention to the issue. They alleged that the State was getting ready to close down hundreds of hostels belonging to SC, ST, BC and minorities, blaming the hostel wardens and social welfare officials for the pathetic situation.